1.40pm That South Africa are still in this game is largely down to Kyle Abbott and what he did last evening. He has proved repeatedly, in basketball terms, he is one of the best sixth men out there.

Sam: "Kyle Abbott has bowled 24.5% of the overs in this innings so far and has conceded only 38 runs while taking half of the wickets. "

1.30pm Advantage Australia. South Africa has a lot to do to return this game to deuce. Yesterday was all about Usman Khawaja and one of the best Australian hundreds in recent years. Australia lead by 48 with four wickets in hand. A lead of close to 100 is not going to be easy to come back from.

Like his debut, Khawaja has found himself batting for a team in tribulation. Unlike his debut, he has responded with something of genuine substance. He has earned the right to respect, writes Dan Brettig.
